# PUBLIC Quarto and PRIVATE Knowledge Graph


## Step 1: Obsidian Setup


## Step 2: Quarto Setup

Run the creation command directly inside your root workspace directory. Use the --no-run-runtime flag to prevent it from stalling on environment checks, and specify the website type:

```bash
quarto create project website .
```
What to expect: Quarto will scan the directory, see your existing setup, and generate its boilerplate configuration files. It will explicitly create or attempt to overwrite _quarto.yml, index.qmd, about.qmd, styles.css, and .gitignore.

### Step 2 Extra: Use Git to Revert Overwritten Configurations

Because Quarto's default templates will update the specific path exclusions needed to shield your private brain/ graph and .obsidian configurations, use Git immediately to inspect.

```bash
PS Q:\__writing__\_LLM_wiki_\LLM-wiki-quarto> quarto create project website .
? Title (website) » LLM-wiki-quarto
Creating project at Q:\__writing__\_LLM_wiki_\LLM-wiki-quarto:
  - Created _quarto.yml
  - Created .gitignore
  - Created index.qmd
  - Created about.qmd
  - Created styles.css
```


